# Azure App Registration Credentials
# Get these values from your Azure App Registration in the Azure Portal
# https://portal.azure.com -> Azure Active Directory -> App registrations

# Your App Registration Client ID (Application ID)
AZURE_CLIENT_ID=your-app-registration-client-id-here

# Your App Registration Client Secret (create one in "Certificates & secrets")
AZURE_CLIENT_SECRET=your-app-registration-client-secret-here

# Your Azure Tenant ID (Directory ID)
AZURE_TENANT_ID=your-azure-tenant-id-here

# Optional: Specific scopes (defaults to https://graph.microsoft.com/.default)
# AZURE_SCOPES=https://graph.microsoft.com/.default

# How to get these values:
# 1. Go to https://portal.azure.com
# 2. Navigate to Azure Active Directory > App registrations
# 3. Create a new registration or select existing one
# 4. Copy the "Application (client) ID" -> AZURE_CLIENT_ID
# 5. Copy the "Directory (tenant) ID" -> AZURE_TENANT_ID
# 6. Go to "Certificates & secrets" > "Client secrets" > "New client secret"
# 7. Copy the secret value (not the ID) -> AZURE_CLIENT_SECRET
# 8. Grant appropriate Microsoft Graph permissions in "API permissions"
#    - For delta queries: Application.Read.All, User.Read.All, Group.Read.All, etc.
